<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 <gloss target="#t_PAA1">PAA</gloss>/10–1047: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                                    Argentina</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-10T15:00:00-05:00">October
                                    10, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>960. <gloss target="#t_Panagra1">Panagra</gloss> has advised Dept they
                            have dispatched air mail letter to their representatives <gloss target="#t_BA1">BA</gloss> authorizing, if not instructing, them to
                            inform <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss> Govt, of company’s future
                            operating plans in <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss>. Briefly, these
                            plans include inauguration about Nov 1 non-stop services Lima–<gloss target="#t_BA1">BA</gloss> and eventual elimination all <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss> stops except <gloss target="#t_BA1">BA</gloss>.</p>
                        <p>It is suggested <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> contact local <gloss target="#t_Panagra1">Panagra</gloss> and discuss advisability (pro
                            and con) divulging such <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> to <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss> until really necessary, or route
                            negotiations settled, whichever sooner. Dept unable cite any specific
                            reasons withhold carrier’s plans at this time but believes question
                            should be weighed by <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> in light
                            possible effect upon current <gloss target="#t_Arg1">Arg</gloss>
                            consideration route patterns.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>